The paper deals with motion planning for autonomous robots, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The method proposed in the paper involves predicting the map of the unobserved environment using data-driven techniques, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of heuristics for navigation, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with safe navigation of robots, which is a key concern in control systems (cs.SY).
